<br>
1. There is a building in FV if you go right upon entering the city (near the water) with an ogre, dwarf, and a woman holding a sword.  Talk to the woman and go through the responses (She talks about the wurmslayer quest).<br>
<br>
2. Exit the city and hang around the stone path (the portion of the path that is in between the bridge to FV and the river), this is where I have seen Hobble spawn several times.<br>
<br>
3. If you don't see Hobble in 15-20 mins, repeat step 1.  I spawned Hobble twice in a few hours using this method (he died the first time).  Not sure if I was lucky, or if step 1. really helped.  This is just my personal experience.<br>
<br>
4. If you see Hobble, it is important to note that if he gets near the tunnel to DL, it's over.  He will die and you will probably die trying to save him.  He will almost assuredly aggro a spider long before he gets there though.  Hail him immediately (to spawn the squire.  It will take the squire a couple mins to run out to Hobble).  When Hobble aggros a spider, taunt it off him and get it aggroed on you, then pull the spider back close to the bridge.  The goal is to keep Hobble as far away from the DL tunnel (and the massive amounts of spiders there) as possible.<br>
<br>
5.  Make sure your 3 scales are easily accessible in your inventory slots so you can turn them in very quickly.<br>
<br>
6. The squire will not stop running if you hail him.  You will need to turn the scales in on the move.  I was not sowed when I did this and was able to turn in all 3 in one shot.  Turning them in one at a time will work though.  However, you don't want to turn in one or 2, then have him die. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
7.  Make sure you have an open inventory slot for the WS.<br>
<br>
Enjoy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
