<br>
Need 2 characters to do this my way (much easier than any other way out there).<br>
<br>
Ranger/Bard/Druid (tracking Hobble)<br>
Enchanter (mezzing Hobble)<br>
<br>
Enchanter is set up near beach, a short way away from FV (no wandering mobs there).<br>
Tracker runs up and down road until Sir Hobble on Tracking.  When Hobble is located he will be:<br>
1) wandering<br>
2) fighting<br>
<br>
If 1), Tracker runs up to Sir Hobble and hails him until you get the response back.  Then you whack Sir Hobble and run back to chanter.<br>
<br>
If 2), You have two choices, help Sir Hobble kill the mob, or try to get agro on you.  If you help him kill mob, wait til done fighting, hail, whack him and run to chanter.  If you try and pull him away from mobs, run back to chanter once agro on you.  (You can snare other mob to keep it from catching Hobble)<br>
<br>
When you bring Sir Hobble back to chanter, chanter will mez him.  Have tracker camp out to clear agro.  If Hobble hasn't been properly &quot;hailed&quot; yet (gotten back a response), then the chanter can camp out to clear agro also and come back and hail him.<br>
<br>
When you &quot;hail&quot; Sir Hobble and get a response, Fuzzman spawns and will start heading to Hobble.  The chanter can continue to keep Sir Hobble mezzed and Fuzzman will not attack the chanter.  Fuzzman will just stand next to Hobble waiting to give you your Wurmslayer.  Make sure you have an open inventory slot (will not fit in regular backpack).<br>
<br>
I have kept Hobble mezzed for over 45 minutes while waiting for a couple guildmates to log on and head over to FV.  Have used the same Fuzzman to get 4 Wurmslayers.<br>
<br>
Getting scales:<br>
<br>
Gullerbak is PH for Azdalin<br>
Entalon is PH for Gylton<br>
<br>
X scale - 2 ways to get this.  Kill guy in Temple for scale or do a simple quest.  To do quest the easy way you need a druid and a character non-KoS in OT.   Can use a lvl 1 human necro, start in Freeport, run to Oasis and take boat to OT.  Get a bind in OT.   Have druid bind outside OT city wall (in corner where no mobs wander).  Druid will carry gems for doing quest.  Give gems to necro.  Necro does quest and runs back to druid.  Druid group TP's to Lava.  Both run to temple.  Druid hands necro gem.  Necro turns in quest item and gem to mob in temple to get scale.  Necro hands X scale to druid or a mule standing by.  Necro attacks mob to get killed and get a free TP back to bind point.  Druid gates back to bind point to start over.  <br>
<br>
You can get about 5 scales an hour doing quest this way.  I was able to trade X scales for the A and G scales and get quite a few Wurmslayers in just  a couple weeks.<br>
